cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the problem of traffic sign detection using computer vision techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of benchmark algorithms, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of simulated challenging conditions to create a new dataset is related to robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the investigation of the effect of challenging conditions on detection performance is related to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category.
